The hardest part was making sure the audit log captured not just what happened but the before and after state of critical data — I used EF Core's ChangeTracker for this, which required careful design to avoid performance overhead.
Result: The system went live and has had zero compliance violations since launch. The compliance team reviewed the audit logs during a formal audit and passed without a single finding. That was the moment I knew the design was right.

